text: Zayed Port () also called Mina Zayed, is a commercial deep-water port owned by the Abu Dhabi Ports that serves Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates. It was established in 1968.http://www.admedia.ae/celebrate40/en/events/event-39 == Geography == Zayed Port has an area of 535 hectares and contains 21 berths with depths ranging from 6-15 metres and a total berth length of 4,375 metres. == References == Category:Geography of the United Arab Emirates
title: Zayed Port
